-- Hong Kong April Visitor Arrivals Rise 12% on Yr to 4.28 Million
-- B y   S a n d i   L i u
-- 2013-05-30T09:41:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-30/hong-kong-april-visitor-arrivals-rise-12-on-yr-to-4-28-million.html
Hong Kong’s visitor arrivals in April
rose 12 percent from a year earlier to 4.28 million, the city’s
Tourism Board said on its website today.  Number of visitors from mainland China rose 18 percent to
3.11 million for the month, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sandi Liu at 
